						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Rājakēsarivarman, •••= c. 10th Century.</p>						

						<p>These are fragments in the tenth-century characters. The first one mentions Chembiyaṉ Indavadi-araiyaṉ making a gift of gold. The second dated in the reign of Rājakēsarivarman refers to a mercenary soldier <hi rend="italic">(kūlichchēvagaṉ).</hi> Other bits mention the temple of Mahādēva at Choḻachūḷamaṇi-chaturvēdimaṅgalam and the ūrār of Peruṅgōḷūr and Chāttaṉūr.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">I</hi></p>						

